# WP-12 trivy escapes (audited 2026-06-10). Both are advisories in the
# exact-pinned langchain-core 1.2.5 with upstream fixes available. Bumping the
# LLM framework pins is a coordinated dependency-finalization change (the
# frozen WP-I contract), not a CI patch — Dependabot (.github/dependabot.yml)
# files those bump PRs weekly. REMOVE each entry when the bump lands.
# Mirrored as --ignore-vuln escapes in the pip-audit step of ci.yml.

# langchain-core 1.2.5 -> fixed in 1.2.22. Path traversal in the LEGACY
# load_prompt() helpers — FinResearchAI never loads prompts from disk paths
# (all prompts are inline string constants in src/agents/*).
CVE-2026-34070

# langchain-core 1.2.5 -> fixed in 1.3.3. Unsafe deserialization via an overly
# broad load()/loads() allowlist — FinResearchAI never deserializes LangChain
# payloads (no load()/loads() callers; structured output goes through Pydantic
# schemas in src/llm/schemas.py).
CVE-2026-44843
